NAN President Muhammadu Buhari approved his re-appointment of Mr. Olusegun Awolowo as the Executive Director and Chief Executive Officer of the Nigerian Export Promotion Council (NEPC). President Buhari’s approval was contained in a statement issued by his Special Adviser on media and publicity, Mr. Femi Adesina, on Wednesday. He said in the statement that a letter signed by  Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Mr. Boss Mustapha, said the appointment lasts for four years. Awolowo, a lawyer and scion of the Obafemi Awolowo family, was first appointed to the NEPC position in 2013.